  <data name="TextBox1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>How to play the Game

Player1
This player instigates the game. At the beginning of each game, player 1 is the first player, regardless of who has won the previous game.
At the beginning of each round, before player 1 has pressed the load button, player 1 decides which type of game this round will be played
in. There are 3 types of game.
1 chamber play, 3 chamber play and 6 chamber play.
1 chamber play is the traditional form of russian roulette. The bullet is placed in a random chamber of the cartridge, the cartridge is spun, and
slamed into engaging with the firing barrel of the pistol. The chamber which engages with the firing barrel is not known, and random. The 
gun is placed toward the head, and the trigger is pulled.
If the gun fails to fire, then you win. If the gun does fire, then you die.
3 chamber play forces the player to fire the gun 3 consecutive times, without spinning the cartridge. This greatly raises the chances of the 
gun firing. However, for one of these times, the player has the option of pointing the gun toward the opponent, and thus if the gun fires, it  
is the opponent who dies instead of the player.
6 chamber play requires all 6 chambers to be fired consecutively. This play ensures a consequence to the round. However during this play, 
you have the option of pointing the gun at your opponent in two, and only two instances.
Which ever play that player 1 decides, player 2 must engage in that same play. After the round, player 1 can choose to change this play if
they choose.

Points for the game.
For each turn, that is, each time that the trigger is pulled but does not fire, the player recieves points. The standard amount of points for 
the survival of a turn is 100 points. If the player is killed, they do not recieve any points for that turn. If the player survives their round 
they recieve extra points. If a player survives a 3 chamber play, they recieve 300 points. If a player survives a 6 chamber play, that is by
killing their opponent, they recieve 600 points.
The surviving player of a game retains there points into the next game, and until they are killed.

